metadata.othernotes:
Critical Darling is at the Inventory as a crazy marketing plan for her band, Melting Dreamscape; she figures people will remember that "rock star" they played strip poker with. The band is currently touring the US in an RV borrowed from Critical Darling's uncle. Their budget is very limited.

She once joined an open super-powered wrestling tournament, "NHBF Wrestling," with a similar plan to build fame for her band. She lost to the now current champion, La Dragonesa, in the semi-finals. Critical Darling isn't under contract with the league and hasn't wrestled since.

Coming from a world full of super heroes and villains, Critical Darling is able to conjure ice, but is neither hero nor villain. She likes to use them during her gigs for special effects. There are schools for people with powers to learn to use them, but she's never attended one.

Both of her parents are Japan-born Japanese, but she herself was born and raised in America. She can speak both English and Japanese fluently. Her extended family lives in Yokohama, Japan, whom she frequently visits.

Her fetishes are breast play and dildo play. She's put off by the idea of oral and anal.

Target-worthy things:

Critical Darling is not interested in using her powers to fight crime. She believes she'd just get herself killed trying to play hero, and would much rather use them to entertain.

She has no idea where her powers come from, they simply appeared one day. She's unsure whether they're a mutation, a dormant trait, or a form of magic.

She's mildly insecure about her breast size and thinks her own vagina is gross (just hers, not others').

case.name: No One Knows My Plan
case.description: Ibuki is here to promot her band, Melting Dreamscape, expecting people to be unable to forget the rock star they played strip poker with.

case.name: NHBF Wrestling
case.description: In addition to being a musician, Ibuki also took part in a wrestling tournament; though, she lost to the current champion, La Dragonesa.

case.name: Wings Of A Dream
case.description: Though she has ice powers, Ibuki wishes she had wings instead.

case.name: Not Super
case.description: Ibuki explains that she knows most people with powers become superheroes, and that she doesn't want to be one herself. She will also mention this if there are any superhero opponents present.

case.name: Duel The Devil?
case.description: Ibuki asks if anyone would risk their soul in a duel with the devil for something.

case.name: Secondary Color
case.description: Though her favorite color is clearly purple, Ibuki will mention that she also loves slime green. Use this as an opportunity to bring up your character's favorite colors.

case.name: Looking For A Band?
case.description: Ibuki asks if anyone is looking to hire an alternative band.

case.name: Death Growl
case.description: Ibuki will occassionally attempt to death growl, always resulting in her coughing from the strain. The marker for this, "DeathGrowl," is incremental, so you can respond to the amount of times she does this in one game.

case.name: Instrument?
case.description: Ibuki mentions that she plays guitar, drums, and keyboard, and asks if anyone else can play anything.

case.name: Through The Fire And
case.description: Ibuki may mention how she can play half of Through The Fire And Flames, her favorite song, on a real guitar (as opposed to in Guitar Hero).

case.name: Mesopotamian Scale
case.description: Ibuki will sometimes rate something "On a scale from Gilgamesh to Hammurabi." If she does, she will later explain it.

case.name: Southpaw
case.description: Ibuki is left-handed. This is noticable whenever she uses her "sing" pose, performing left-handed air guitar.

case.name: Male Stamina?
case.description: Ibuki assumes that all men cum quickly, and will be surprised to see one last more than a few rounds.

case.name: Glasses
case.description: If an opponent is wearing glasses, Ibuki will mention that she technically needs glasses too, but can see fine without them.

case.name: Metal Moods
case.description: Ibuki says that she enjoys how metal guitars can express any mood, and challenges anyone to name a mood that can't be covered by it.

case.name: Heroes & Villains
case.description: Ibuki talks about heroes and villains from her universe.

case.name: Wrestlers
case.description: Ibuki talks about wrestlers that were in the same tournament as her.
